      "id": "be9db314_5dd56839",
      "file_path": "services/services-onappf/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/apex/starter/ApexStarterConstants.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 27,
      "message": "question: Do all of these really need to be added to the registry?  Can some be passed to constructors instead?  For instance, could pass the status object to PdpMessageHandler, rather than having it use the registry.\n\nIn general, the registry should only be used when there's no simple mechanism to communicate info from one object to another.  For instance, there isn't a convenient way to pass objects to the rest servers, thus whatever they need, they must get from the registry.  However, most other objects can be provided via constructors or via setXxx methods.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2019-04-04 22:01:16.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
